<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-162-488  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 162 488.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  Jan 31 1990 n125 p99(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The Micro Touch. (Hardware Review) (Micro Touch trackball)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Beattie, Rob.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Matrix North (products).andO;Product:   Matrix North Micro Touch (Cursor control device) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     TrackballsCursor Control DevicesEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   User verdict. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>The Micro TouchandM;The Micro Touch gets off to a dodgy start by referring you to a test filethat isn't actually on the supplied disk.andP;  In theory, this file is supposedto deduce which serial port you're plugged into -- which is a good idea, butnot if you don't get the disk.andP;  Instead, you get a different file called TESTwhich allows you to check whether or not the tracker ball's two huge buttonsare working properly.andM;There's no on-screen hint as to what you're supposed to do if it doesn't workproperly and it took a certain amount of guesswork before I discovered theculprit was the Apricot mouse driver in my CONFIG.SYS file.andP;  Once I'd made abackup of that and then erased the guilty line, I was able to invokeMOUSE.COM which is supplied on disk and make the tracker ball wake up andwork properly.andM;The theory behind a tracker ball is that it's supposed to take up less spacethan a conventional mouse but be just as easy to use.andP;  Certainly, because theball rolls rather than the entire unit, it'll work even on my ridiculouslycluttered desk.andP;  So too, however, will my mouse which I've now got used tolifting up and down in a stroking movement when piles of paper restrict theamount of desk space I have available.andP;  Physically, the Micro Touch is alargish box about the size of a kid's joystick.andP;  It's raised away from you sothe palm of your hand rests comfortably at the bottom leaving your fingersfree to manipulate the ball and press the twin buttons.andP;  The default speed ofthe cursor - or arrow, depending on your application - is a bit sluggish, butyou can alter its sensitivity by entering a declaration after the MOUSE.COMcommand.andP;  This is OK, but it's a bit arcane and matters aren't helped by thefact that the manual is a crummy typewritten, saddle stitched (stapled)affair, with tiny type, no illustrations and no index.andP;  If somebody at MatrixNorth were- to actually address this problem, the company would make a muchbetter first impression.andM;As it was, the product didn't make much of an impression.andP;  It worked with GEMand Windows products, but the company hadn't included the additional driversrequired to support standard programs like Lotus 1-2-3, SuperCalc, dBase andWordPerfect.andO;</TEXT></DOC>